  "body": "```\r\nError: Transaction reverted for an unrecognized reason. Please report this to help us improve Hardhat.\r\n      at TransparentUpgradeableProxy._delegate (contracts/test.sol:84)\r\n      at TransparentUpgradeableProxy._delegate (contracts/test.sol:84)\r\n      at TransparentUpgradeableProxy._fallback (contracts/test.sol:109)\r\n      at Reflecter.reflect (contracts/test.sol:53)\r\n      at Shooter.shoot (contracts/test.sol:30)\r\n      at TransparentUpgradeableProxy._delegate (contracts/test.sol:84)\r\n      at TransparentUpgradeableProxy._fallback (contracts/test.sol:109)\r\n      at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:97:5)\r\n      at EthModule._sendTransactionAndReturnHash (node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/eth.ts:1282:9)\r\n      at HardhatNetworkProvider.request (node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/provider.ts:101:14)\r\n      at EthersProviderWrapper.send (node_modules/@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers/src/ethers-provider-wrapper.ts:13:20)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error takes place when\r\n- 1. [upgradeable proxy](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/proxy/UpgradeableProxy.soll) is used and\r\n- 2. during the message call to external contract, the external contract `transfer` ether to proxy contract\r\n\r\nThe underlying problem is actually `OutOfGas` error since `transfer` only provides limited amount of gas for the callee and the gas is just not enough for proxy to further delegate the call. If `transfer` is changed to `.call{value: â€¦}(\"\")` it will work.",
